. do 06-extracting-categories-with-extract.do 

. *****************************************************************************
> ***
. * 06-extracting-categories-with-extract.do
. *
. * Discover a category scheme with `catllm extract`. Use this when you
. * have free-text data and no pre-defined coding scheme -- let the model
. * surface the recurring themes for you.
. *
. * Behind the scenes, extract() chunks your data, runs the discovery
. * prompt multiple times (across `iterations`), merges semantically
. * similar labels, and returns a ranked list of top categories.
. *
. * Compare this to example 04, which is end-to-end (extract -> classify).
. * This example focuses on the tuning knobs of extract itself.
. *
. * Requires: OPENAI_API_KEY
. * Cost:     ~$0.10 (two extract runs at different specificity)
. * Runtime:  ~1 minute
. *****************************************************************************
> ***
. 
. clear all

. set more off

. 
. adopath + "`c(pwd)'/.."
  [1]  (BASE)      "/Applications/StataNow/ado/base/"
  [2]  (SITE)      "/Applications/StataNow/ado/site/"
  [3]              "."
  [4]  (PERSONAL)  "/Users/chrissoria/Documents/Stata/ado/personal/"
  [5]  (PLUS)      "/Users/chrissoria/Library/Application Support/Stata/ado/plu
> s/"
  [6]  (OLDPLACE)  "~/ado/"
  [7]              "/Users/chrissoria/Documents/Research/cat-llm/stata-package/
> examples/.."

. 
. global OPENAI_API_KEY : env OPENAI_API_KEY

. if "$OPENAI_API_KEY" == "" {
.     di as error "OPENAI_API_KEY not set."
.     exit 198
. }

. 
. * --- Example data: a mixed bag of neighborhood comments --------------------
> --
. input str200 response

                                                                               
>                                                                              
>                                          response
  1. "Just had the best coffee ever! Highly recommend the new place downtown."
  2. "The bus was 40 minutes late again. Public transit here is a joke."
  3. "Loved the museum exhibit on California water rights."
  4. "Why is rent so expensive in this neighborhood?"
  5. "Tried the new ramen spot -- totally worth the wait."
  6. "Construction noise on 4th street has been brutal lately."
  7. "The library's new author series is amazing."
  8. "Need to find an affordable place before lease ends."
  9. "Saw a great documentary at the indie theater last night."
 10. "Trash pickup hasn't come in three weeks. Calling 311."
 11. end

. 
. * --- 1. Basic extract ------------------------------------------------------
> --
. di _n "{hline 60}"

